Diversity is not prevalent in tech with studies showing the current state is abysmal even with tech companies aware of the benefits of having an inclusive workplace. Advertising or the lack there of years ago has caused a gender gap in tech with over 70% of the workforce male, out of that 61% is white. Reasons why diversity matters in tech, diverse teams are smarter and more creative, diverse companies perform better, companies are losing out on great talent, diverse companies can better serve a diverse user base. 11 of the 25 best paying jobs are tech related with average salaries over $100k, STEM classes need to be offered at underrepresented minority schools to get more students in diverse areas interested in tech and available to join the workforce to change demographics for years to come. 
